    <stitle>T 444E Diesel Engine Diagnostics (NAVPAK) (1997) - SECTION 3.5: ELECTRONIC CONTROL SYSTEM DIAGNOSTICS,
        ACCELERATOR PEDAL POSITION SENSOR/IVS SWITCH (APS/IVS) - V REF VOLTAGE REFERENCE - FAULT DETECTION/MANAGEMENT
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="PROCTYPE" graphiccount="1">
        <title>FAULT DETECTION/MANAGEMENT</title>
        <para>There is no fault detection specifically for the V Ref signal directly, but if there is a V Ref circuit
            fault the sensor(s) in the section of the circuit affected may set an out of range high or low code.
            Multiple high or low codes are usually an indication of a V Ref or in some instances a Signal Ground fault
            condition.
        </para>
        <para>A V Ref signal shorted to ground will cause the ECM to reset causing either a stumble or no start
            condition.
        </para>
        <para>Refer to
            <emph type="BOLD">Figure
                <hotlnk xrefid="f19017131">3.108</hotlnk>
            </emph>
            for the voltage reference circuit diagram and
            <emph type="BOLD">Table
                <hotlnk xrefid="f19017132">3.35</hotlnk>
            </emph>
            for the connector checks.
        </para>
